{
  "stem": "4963.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I had-- they put makeup on me so that I would look older, because I was only 14.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I had high heels and-- and a coat.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It was winter.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I remember it was very cold.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I went out in the workforce and then-- we had-- we were-- Which you hadn't been doing.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, that was my first time that I was in the workforce.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But, again, I approached everything as an exciting, you know, going to a-- some interesting adventure.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were wearing the [INAUDIBLE], you know, yellow [INAUDIBLE] back on-- on the left, so close to our heart, as they said, and on the-- in the back on the left side as well.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that was one of the-- one of the things that-- that we had to-- that my aunts coached me on how to take it off.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they were-- they were with-- they were with-- they were tacked on with-- with a pin so that when-- you know, I had to practice how to remove that back and-- from the front and from the back so that I would-- the only way you could go out of the workforce was to smuggle yourself out of the-- you know, to sort of position yourself in the front line and quickly find a place where you saw so many Lithuanians going by and throw yourself into that group of Lithuanians so that-- you know, without the Germans seeing you.",
      "word_count": 101
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Now there were-- I remember very distinctly, those Germans who were-- or the Lithuanians-- going every three rows.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They were right there with a gun ready to shoot, which they did anytime someone escaped from the lineup.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So I approached that, again, as an exciting event.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was never afraid.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
